# Cloudflare Workers/Pages static-assets header rules.
#
# Cross-origin isolation is what lets the Cloudflare mirror run the
# multithreaded (MT) WASM engine: SharedArrayBuffer (required by Emscripten
# pthreads — see orca-wasm/MT-PLAN.md) is only available on a page where
# self.crossOriginIsolated is true, which requires both headers below on
# every document/worker response. GitHub Pages (the primary deployment)
# cannot send custom response headers at all, so it stays ST-only regardless
# — this file only affects the Cloudflare mirror, and is a no-op there
# (ignored) if wrangler ever changes hosts.
#
# COEP require-corp still lets this page load slicer-mt.wasm cross-origin
# from GitHub Pages: that response already carries
# Access-Control-Allow-Origin: * (verified live), which satisfies COEP for a
# CORS-mode fetch even without an explicit Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy
# header on the GitHub Pages side.
/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
